                <p>Children learn better in peer environments. Parents should encourage their kids to attend Quran study groups at the mosque or join online sessions at <a href="https://www.dararqam.com"><strong style="color: #800080; font-size: 18px; font-family: 'Reem Kufi';">Dar Arqam</strong></a>. These platforms create a sense of community, helping children stay motivated and engaged.</p>
                <p><a href="https://www.dararqam.com"><strong style="color: #800080; font-size: 18px; font-family: 'Reem Kufi';">Dar Arqam</strong></a>'s virtual group classes allow kids to connect with peers worldwide, ensuring a fun and interactive learning experience.</p>
            </div>

